Elena Kagan, in her opening statement before the Senate Judiciary Committee, expressed her belief in the importance of the rule of law and the role of the Supreme Court in safeguarding it. She emphasized the idea of equal justice for all and the need for judges to be even-handed and impartial. Kagan also acknowledged the importance of the democratic process and the Court's responsibility to respect the choices made by the American people. She highlighted the value of listening to different perspectives and approaching issues with an open mind. Kagan pledged to remember and abide by these principles if confirmed, promising to listen to every party before the Court, work hard, and consider every case impartially and in accordance with the law.